Train Collision Prevention System using Hall Effect Sensors

An Arduino-based railway safety prototype that detects train movement, controls railway signals, regulates train speed, and automatically stops the train under unsafe conditions using Hall Effect sensors.

Overview

Railway collisions are one of the major safety concerns in transportation systems. This project presents a low-cost embedded solution that continuously monitors train movement using Hall Effect sensors and automatically controls railway signals and train speed.

The system uses an Arduino Uno as the main controller. Three Hall Effect sensors act as checkpoints along the track to determine the train's position. Based on sensor inputs, the controller updates signal indications, regulates the train's speed through PWM, and triggers an emergency stop if the train fails to reach the next checkpoint within a predefined time interval.

The prototype also includes an automated railway crossing gate operated by a servo motor, demonstrating how embedded systems can improve both railway and road safety.

