Working Principle
Step 1

The Hall Effect sensors continuously monitor the train's movement.

↓

Step 2

Whenever a train crosses a checkpoint, the Arduino determines its current position.

↓

Step 3

The railway signals are updated.

🟢 Green → Track Clear
🟡 Yellow → Caution
🔴 Red → Stop

↓

Step 4

The DC motor speed is adjusted using PWM.

Safe Track

Motor Speed = Full

Caution Zone

Motor Speed = Reduced

Danger

Motor = OFF

↓

Step 5

The Arduino continuously checks the elapsed time using the millis() function.

If the train does not reach the next Hall Effect sensor within 7 seconds,

All signals become RED
Motor stops
Collision prevention routine activates

↓

Step 6

A separate Hall Effect sensor detects an approaching train at the crossing.

The servo motor lowers the gate automatically and raises it after the train passes.

